            <thetext>The global namespace pollution detection of qx.dev.Pollution did not keep up with recent developments in browsers and other JavaScript environments. As a result, the detection is flawed with false negatives or positives depending on the code you put under test.

With today&#39;s JavaScript debugging tools such as Firebug, there are more reliable ways to detect global namespace pollution. Moreover, a JavaScript code quality checker (lint) is included in qooxdoo&#39;s tool chain making the detection virtually useless.

We have therefore decided to deprecate qx.dev.Pollution.</thetext>
